```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_mcp_ui_runtime/flutter_mcp_ui_runtime.dart';
import 'bundle.g.dart' show kBundle;

Future<void> main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();
  final runtime = MCPUIRuntime();
  await runtime.initialize(kBundle);
  runApp(runtime.buildRoot());
}
```
No host MCP server needed for the standalone — tools dispatch through the runtime's in-process executor.

App Builder builtin exposes 2 host tools at port 7831:
- app_builder.newAppProject - new workspace project (with/without dialog)
- app_builder.dispatch_builder_tool {name, args} - passthrough to active mount in-process MCP server. Single channel for all vibe_* mutators.

Host side (studio.*):
- studio.chrome.{list_tabs, select_tab, reload_tab}
- studio.project.{info, close, new, open, recents}
- studio.bundle.{install, activate, list, uninstall, read_file, list_files}
- studio.debug.{screenshot, runtime_state, dispatch_log, boot_log}

External LLM permission = MCP surface only. Local cat/ls/rm/find, code edits, infra ops forbidden.
